Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_aocv_interface_path_offset(25.10)    set_aocv_interface_path_offset(25.10)

Name
       set_aocv_interface_path_offset - You can perform path-based inter power
       domain  (IPD)  timing analysis by specifying derate offset value for an
       entire power domain(s) and specific library cell(s) on  paths  crossing
       multiple power domains

Syntax
       set_aocv_interface_path_offset

       <derateOffsetVal>

       [<lib_cells>]

       [-view <view_name>]

       [-delay_corner <dc_corner_name>]

       [-cell]

       [-net]

       -power_domain <power_domain_name_list>

       You  can perform path-based inter power domain (IPD) timing analysis by
       specifying derate offset value for an entire power domain(s)  and  spe-
       cific  library  cell(s)  on paths crossing multiple power domains. This
       feature is supported for path-based analysis (PBA) mode only.

       The set_aocv_interface_path_offset command allows you  to  specify  the
       derate  offset value for path segments crossing multiple power domains.
       The software adds the derate offset value to the AOCV derate  value  if
       the  combined  (AOCV + IPD offset) derate number causes pessimistic PBA
       timing slack value.

Parameters
       -cell  It is a boolean option. When the -cell option is specified,  in-
              tent is to apply "derate offset" only for that cell objects.

              In absence of these options, derate offset value will be applied
              to both cell and net type of objects

       -delay_corner <dc_corner_name>
              Specifies a list of delay corners.

       <derateOffsetVal>
              Specifies value of derate offset.

       <lib_cells>
              Specifies a list of library cells for a specific interface.

       -net   It  is  a boolean option. When the -net option is specified, in-
              tent is to apply "derate offset" only for that net objects.

       In absence of these options, derate offset value  will  be  applied  to
       both cell and net type of objects

       -power_domain <power_domain_name_list>
              Specifies a list of power domains.

       -view<view_name>
              Specifies a list of views.

Examples
              * The  following  example  specifies  the offset derate value of
                -0.6 for the power domain {PD3 PD4}:

                set_aocv_interface_path_offset -0.6  -power_domain  {PD3  PD4}
                -delay_corner V1_PM1_dc

